📅 Class Routine Management System - Functional & UI Specification

This document details the user roles, capabilities, and screen designs for the Class Routine Management System.

🎭 Role-Based Job Descriptions

1️⃣ DEPARTMENT ADMIN

Role: The primary manager of the schedule.
📌 Responsibilities:

A. Time Slot Management:

Create new time slots (e.g., 8:00-8:50, 8:50-9:40).

Edit/Delete existing time slots.

Define Break Times and Lunch Times separately.

Change class duration (50 mins / 60 mins / 90 mins).

B. Room Management:

View Room List (All rooms with capacity and type).

Add new rooms.

Set Room Features (Projector available, AC, Lab equipment).

Mark rooms as temporarily unavailable.

View Room-wise Schedule (See what is happening in a specific room at any time).

C. Teacher & Course Assignment:

Select which teacher takes which course.

Assign multiple teachers to the same course (e.g., separate teachers for Theory & Lab).

View Teacher Preferences (Preferred/Unpreferred times).

View Total Workload (Classes per week to prevent burnout).

D. Create Class Schedule (Core Task):

Manual Mode: Drag-and-drop classes into slots.

Quick Assign: Schedule all classes for a specific course at once.

Template Use: Copy schedule from a previous semester.

Select Course + Teacher + Room + Day + Time simultaneously.

Set Weekly Patterns (Repeat same time every week).

E. Conflict Management:

View all types of conflicts:

Same teacher assigned to two places at once.

Same room booked for two classes at once.

Student Batch Conflict (Section A has 2 classes at the same time).

Auto-suggestion: Receive AI suggestions for alternative slots to resolve conflicts.

Ignore Conflict: Override warnings (if intentional).

F. Reschedule Request Management:

View reschedule requests from teachers.

Approve or Reject requests.

Suggest alternative slots back to the teacher.

G. Publish & Distribution:

Work in "Draft Mode" initially.

Publish to users after review.

Export to PDF/Excel.

Send notifications to all stakeholders.

2️⃣ TEACHER

Role: The executor of the classes.
📌 Responsibilities:

A. View Own Schedule:

View weekly classes in List or Grid view.

Filter by day (Today's classes, Tomorrow's classes).

Class Details: Course Name, Section, Room Number, Time, Number of Students Enrolled.

B. Set Availability:

Click on a calendar view to mark status:

✅ Available

❌ Unavailable (Must provide reason: meeting, research, personal).

⭐ Preferred (Ideally wants class at this time).

Set recurring unavailability (e.g., Unavailable every Tuesday 1-2 PM).

C. Send Reschedule Request:

Select specific class to reschedule.

Provide reason (Meeting, Sick Leave, Conference).

Suggest Preferred Alternative Time.

Track Request Status (Pending/Approved/Rejected).

D. Download & Export:

Download schedule as PDF.

Download in iCalendar format (for Google Calendar/Outlook).

Weekly/Monthly print view.

E. Notifications:

Alerts when the schedule changes.

Notification when a new class is assigned.

Notification on Reschedule Approval/Rejection.

❌ Restrictions:

Cannot view or edit other teachers' schedules.

Cannot change Rooms or Time Slots directly.

Cannot modify Course Offerings.

Cannot delete any schedule.

3️⃣ STUDENT

Role: The consumer of the schedule.
📌 Responsibilities:

A. View Own Routine:

View full weekly routine based on Batch/Section.

View Modes:

📅 Weekly Grid View: Full week at a glance.

📋 List View: Chronological list.

📆 Day View: Focus on today.

Class Info: Course Code/Name, Teacher Name, Room/Building, Time, Type (Lecture/Lab).

B. Filter & Search:

Search for specific courses.

View classes for specific days.

Find classes by Teacher name.

C. Download Options:

PDF Download (Print-friendly).

iCalendar format.

Direct Google Calendar Sync button.

Screenshot-friendly view.

D. Class Status:

Notification + Crossed-out mark for Cancelled classes.

Highlighted new time for Rescheduled classes.

Current/Today's classes highlighted.

E. Reschedule Vote (Optional Feature):

Vote on new times if a teacher requests a reschedule.

Select preferred slot.

❌ Restrictions:

Cannot edit any schedule.

Cannot view other sections (unless allowed).

Cannot change Room or Teacher.

No administrative capabilities.

4️⃣ SUPER ADMIN

Role: System overseer.
📌 Responsibilities:

A. System-wide Control:

View schedules of ALL departments.

Edit any department's schedule.

View Cross-Department Conflicts (regarding shared resources/rooms).

B. Configuration:

Global Settings: Set default class duration.

Enforce Break Times across all departments.

Manage Academic Calendar.

Set Holidays/Exam Schedules (Applicable to all).

C. Reports & Analytics:

Schedule Summary for all departments.

Room Utilization Report: Heatmap of room usage.

Teacher Workload Report: Identify overloaded teachers.

Conflict Statistics.

D. Audit & Logs:

Track who changed what and when.

Monitor unauthorized changes.

